{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"760b24b5-83b8-4f7d-84e2-db2ef756c496","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility bridge by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK shipped both Microsoft.Testing.Platform **and** the VSTest bridge adapter, so `vstest.console` could still discover tests. Starting with 4.0, `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge` defaults to `false`, meaning `vstest.console` sees no tests.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n**Option A — Re-enable the bridge** (quick fix):\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Option B — Migrate your CI to use `dotnet test`** (recommended long-term):\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n\n`dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively and doesn't need the VSTest bridge at all. This is the direction MSTest is heading.\n\nWould you like me to update your `.csproj` with Option A?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"eaa97741-8c25-421d-8008-1139b19863c3","outputTokens":305,"requestId":"3411:47F73:F978B0:125D2CD:69F4163B"},"id":"13f96ecd-d67d-4b78-8aa2-c18dfb441507","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:56:04.239Z","parentId":"2e7634a3-eaa6-4f42-b623-f7508cbc06bf"}
